{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Amend Welsh devolution settlement to remove control over spending on roads",
        "additional_details": "Removing control from the Welsh Senedd and Welsh Government over spending on road infrastructure will allow the UK Government and Parliament to control this spending instead.\r\n \r\nThis would mean the UK Government could ensure Wales has a modern, up to date road infrastructure, such as a third Menai Crossing. We believe this could help bring about vastly increased business opportunities and income from tourism for Wales and the UK as a whole.\r\n",
        "background": "We want to have the UK Government and Parliament amend the devolution settlement for Wales to remove control over spending on road infrastructure from the Welsh Senedd and Welsh Government.",
